author: @castleofmyskin
text: What makes Toxic beloved is his believability: there's no affect, no hyperbole, no trite, no overkill. HipHop is not just about realness but about the skills to convey one's world as a living tissue. I just moved back from the States where I was a hiphop head for many years and what i respect about Toxic is his skills, skills that offer a sembalnce of his lived reality and imagined wealth; I grew up in Umoja 2 when Kayole was in its infancy & there's something novel about Toxic's music, about the realness he conveys, in his grittiness.  He's a technical rapper and that doesn't get the respect it deserves because of all the sheng and the background of his music. There's no really magic formula when it comes to believability: either you convey your reality, however imagined, or lived, with skills or you rap endless nonsense like some rappers we all know.
